21/* Before including this file, you should define a macro:
22
23 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, NAME, CLASS, TYPE, LIBTYPE, BOTH_P,
24 FALLBACK_P, NONANSI_P, ATTRS, IMPLICIT, COND)
25
26 This macro will be called once for each builtin function. The
27 ENUM will be of type `enum built_in_function', and will indicate
28 which builtin function is being processed. The NAME of the builtin
29 function (which will always start with `__builtin_') is a string
30 literal. The CLASS is of type `enum built_in_class' and indicates
31 what kind of builtin is being processed.
32
33 Some builtins are actually two separate functions. For example,
34 for `strcmp' there are two builtin functions; `__builtin_strcmp'
35 and `strcmp' itself. Both behave identically. Other builtins
36 define only the `__builtin' variant. If BOTH_P is TRUE, then this
37 builtin has both variants; otherwise, it is has only the first
38 variant.
39
40 TYPE indicates the type of the function. The symbols correspond to
41 enumerals from builtin-types.def. If BOTH_P is true, then LIBTYPE
42 is the type of the non-`__builtin_' variant. Otherwise, LIBTYPE
43 should be ignored.
44
45 If FALLBACK_P is true then, if for some reason, the compiler cannot
46 expand the builtin function directly, it will call the
47 corresponding library function (which does not have the
48 `__builtin_' prefix.
49
50 If NONANSI_P is true, then the non-`__builtin_' variant is not an
51 ANSI/ISO library function, and so we should pretend it does not
52 exist when compiling in ANSI conformant mode.
53
54 ATTRs is an attribute list as defined in builtin-attrs.def that
55 describes the attributes of this builtin function.
56
57 IMPLICIT specifies condition when the builtin can be produced by
58 compiler. For instance C90 reserves floorf function, but does not
59 define it's meaning. When user uses floorf we may assume that the
60 floorf has the meaning we expect, but we can't produce floorf by
61 simplifying floor((double)float) since the runtime need not implement
62 it.
63
64 The builtins is registered only if COND is true. */
65
66/* A macro for builtins where the
67 BUILT_IN_*_CHKP = BUILT_IN_* + BEGIN_CHKP_BUILTINS + 1
68 enums should be defined too. */
69#ifndef DEF_BUILTIN_CHKP
70#define DEF_BUILTIN_CHKP(ENUM, NAME, CLASS, TYPE, LIBTYPE, BOTH_P, \
71 FALLBACK_P, NONANSI_P, ATTRS, IMPLICIT, COND) \
72 DEF_BUILTIN(ENUM, NAME, CLASS, TYPE, LIBTYPE, BOTH_P, FALLBACK_P, \
73 NONANSI_P, ATTRS, IMPLICIT, COND)
74#endif

76/* A GCC builtin (like __builtin_saveregs) is provided by the
77 compiler, but does not correspond to a function in the standard
78 library. */

81 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, BT_LAST, \
82 false, false, false, ATTRS, true, true)

103/* A library builtin (like __builtin_strchr) is a builtin equivalent
104 of an ANSI/ISO standard library function. In addition to the
105 `__builtin' version, we will create an ordinary version (e.g,
106 `strchr') as well. If we cannot compute the answer using the
107 builtin function, we will fall back to the standard library
108 version. */
109#undef DEF_LIB_BUILTIN
110#define DEF_LIB_BUILTIN(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
111 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, TYPE, \
112 true, true, false, ATTRS, true, true)
113#undef DEF_LIB_BUILTIN_CHKP
114#define DEF_LIB_BUILTIN_CHKP(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
115 DEF_BUILTIN_CHKP (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, \
116 TYPE, true, true, false, ATTRS, true, true)
117
118/* Like DEF_LIB_BUILTIN, except that the function is not one that is
119 specified by ANSI/ISO C. So, when we're being fully conformant we
120 ignore the version of these builtins that does not begin with
121 __builtin. */
122#undef DEF_EXT_LIB_BUILTIN
123#define DEF_EXT_LIB_BUILTIN(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
124 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, TYPE, \
125 true, true, true, ATTRS, false, true)
126#undef DEF_EXT_LIB_BUILTIN_CHKP
127#define DEF_EXT_LIB_BUILTIN_CHKP(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
128 DEF_BUILTIN_CHKP (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, \
129 TYPE, true, true, true, ATTRS, false, true)

180/* Builtin used by the implementation of OpenACC and OpenMP. Few of these are
181 actually implemented in the compiler; most are in libgomp. */
182/* These builtins also need to be enabled in offloading compilers invoked from
183 mkoffload; for that purpose, we're checking the -foffload-abi flag here. */
184#undef DEF_GOACC_BUILTIN
185#define DEF_GOACC_BUILTIN(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
186 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, TYPE, \
187 false, true, true, ATTRS, false, \
188 (flag_openacc \
189 || flag_offload_abi != OFFLOAD_ABI_UNSET))
190#undef DEF_GOACC_BUILTIN_COMPILER
191#define DEF_GOACC_BUILTIN_COMPILER(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
192 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, TYPE, \
193 flag_openacc, true, true, ATTRS, false, true)
194#undef DEF_GOMP_BUILTIN
195#define DEF_GOMP_BUILTIN(ENUM, NAME, TYPE, ATTRS) \
196 DEF_BUILTIN (ENUM, "__builtin_" NAME, BUILT_IN_NORMAL, TYPE, TYPE, \
197 false, true, true, ATTRS, false, \
198 (flag_openacc \
199 || flag_openmp \
200 || flag_tree_parallelize_loops > 1 \
201 || flag_cilkplus \
202 || flag_offload_abi != OFFLOAD_ABI_UNSET))

253/* Define an attribute list for math functions that are normally
254 "impure" because some of them may write into global memory for
255 `errno'. If !flag_errno_math they are instead "const". */
256#undef ATTR_MATHFN_ERRNO
257#define ATTR_MATHFN_ERRNO (flag_errno_math ? \
258 ATTR_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST : ATTR_CONST_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST)
259
260/* Define an attribute list for math functions that are normally
261 "const" but if flag_rounding_math is set they are instead "pure".
262 This distinction accounts for the fact that some math functions
263 check the rounding mode which is akin to examining global
264 memory. */
265#undef ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING
266#define ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING (flag_rounding_math ? \
267 ATTR_PURE_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST : ATTR_CONST_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST)
268
269/* Define an attribute list for math functions that are normally
270 "impure" because some of them may write into global memory for
271 `errno'. If !flag_errno_math, we can possibly use "pure" or
272 "const" depending on whether we care about FP rounding. */
273#undef ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING_ERRNO
274#define ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING_ERRNO (flag_errno_math ? \
275 ATTR_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST : ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING)
276
277/* Define an attribute list for math functions that need to mind FP
278 rounding, but because they store into memory they are never "const"
279 or "pure". Use of this macro is mainly for documentation and
280 maintenance purposes. */
281#undef ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING_STORE
282#define ATTR_MATHFN_FPROUNDING_STORE ATTR_NOTHROW_LEAF_LIST
